abstract: SIOUX CITY, Iowa, June 12.--Two men have just arrived from nine miles north of Sioux City. No details have been received.

abstract: LANCASTER, Penn., June 20.--Jacob Zullinger, aged 14 years, was drowned in the Susquehanna River at Columbia this morning. He was employed at the Susquehanna Rolling Mill and went into the river to swim before working hours.
